She thought about what Lightmare had said to her.
"Lightmare, I'm the misfit of this group, no bot would like me in a billion 
years.  Besides, what about me is there to like? I'm small, I'm a rodent, 
I'm not much of a fighter.  I mean I can fight, but I'm not as strong as say 
you are."

She sighed deeply.

"And no one in thier right mental circiuts would even think of liking me 
like that.  No, Quickstrike isn't my boyfriend.  Right now, I don't think he 
even thinks of me as a friend.  No, I'm under his command and all he wil 
ever do is give me orders and expect me to follow instructions.  If 
Quickstrike is what you seek, then go and seek him.  I will not interfer."

She lowered her head and walked back to the mail part of the cave and sat at 
the computer console.  She whispered to herself, "yup, no bot in his right 
mental circuits would ever like me."
She faced the computer screen and made plans for the hatch cover for the new 
escape tunnel.
